Fragestellungen. So werden die sich wandelnden Identitäten von Stift, Stiftsgemeinschaft und einzelner Frau erfasst und erzählt. Im Blick stehen dabei die gesunden wie kranken Körper der Damen, deren Kleidung, Wohnräume und Räume der Imagination: Lesen, Schreiben, Musizieren, wie auch die prägenden Zeit-Räume wie Tag und Jahr, Lebensalter und Generationenkonflikte, Sterbestunde, Ewigkeit und institutionelle Memoria.  aWhat was the nature of life – and death – in an 18th century Catholic convent? From an anthropological and cultural perspective, Dietmar Schiersner examines the lives of the sisters in sickness and in health, their clothing, living spaces and spaces of the imagination (reading, writing, and music-making), and the rhythms of their lives: days, years, life stages, generational conflicts, the hour of death, eternity, and institutional memorials.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCanonesseszGermanyzAugsburgxHistoryy18th century. 0aCanonesseszGermanyzBavariaxHistoryy18th century. 0aMonastic and religious life of womenzGermanyzAugsburgxHistoryy18th century. 0aMonastic and religious life of womenzGermanyzBavariaxHistoryy18th century. 4aBayerischSchwaben. 4aFrauen in der Kirche. 4aStift. 4aÄbtissin. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 18th Century.2bisacsh  aAbbesses.  aBavaria-Swabia.  aconvent.  awomen in the Church.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2014z9783110370225oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831103929990 cprintz978311034091440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311034106540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110341065423Coveruhttps://www.